cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.HC, cs.CL 

This paper focuses on the interactions between automated software agents (or bots) in Wikipedia, which involves aspects of computer science, social science, and human-computer interaction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), followed by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks). The paper also uses qualitative methods to analyze the interactions, which suggests a possible fit with cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
